{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01M3n5nAY3ewrxX7AsGvw5zB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Definition of Done for a New x-agent\n     2→\n     3→An agent is done only when all items below are complete.\n     4→\n     5→## Skill and Script\n     6→\n     7→- `skills/<name>-agent/SKILL.md` exists with accurate trigger language.\n     8→- `skills/<name>-agent/SKILL.md` `allowed-tools` includes patterns for all env knobs (`RUN_*`, `MAX_LINES`, `KEEP_DIR`, `FAIL_FAST`, plus any agent-specific knobs).\n     9→- `skills/<name>-agent/scripts/<name>-agent.sh` exists and is executable.\n    10→- Script starts with `set -euo pipefail`.\n    11→- Script has `--help`/`help`/`-h` usage output that works without project context (resolved before project-existence checks).\n    12→\n    13→## Output Contract\n    14→\n    15→- Each step emits `Step:`, `Result: PASS|FAIL|SKIP`, and `Time: Xs`.\n    16→- Each `Result: FAIL` is followed by a `Fix:` line — suggests an auto-fix command first (if one exists), then tells how to retest via the agent.\n    17→- On failure, prints truncated diagnostics (first `MAX_LINES` lines) and saves full logs to disk with path printed.\n    18→- Final output is `Overall: PASS|FAIL` and `Logs: <path>`.\n    19→\n    20→## Behavior\n    21→\n    22→- Supports `KEEP_DIR`, `MAX_LINES`, `FAIL_FAST`, `TMPDIR_ROOT`, and `RUN_<STEP>` toggles.\n    23→- `MAX_LINES` defaults to `40` locally, `999999` in CI (`CI=true|1`).\n    24→- CI-sensitive steps adapt behavior (e.g. format: check in CI, fix locally).\n    25→- Accepts `--fail-fast` CLI flag; when set, `all` stops after first failing step.\n    26→- If a downstream tool has native fail-fast support, it is passed through.\n    27→- Required deps checked with `need()` — exits `2` if missing.\n    28→- Missing optional tools are handled as `SKIP` with a clear reason.\n    29→- Cleanup trap preserves logs on failure or `KEEP_DIR=1`; removes temp dir on success.\n    30→- Exit codes: `0` pass, `1` fail, `2` bad usage or missing required dep.\n    31→- Supports `CHANGED_FILES` for scoping work to affected files/packages where meaningful (optional but recommended).\n    32→\n    33→## Documentation and Install\n    34→\n    35→- `README.md` includes the new agent in \"Available Agents\".\n    36→- `README.md` includes basic usage examples for the new script.\n    37→- `install.sh` installs the new skill (update `SKILLS`).\n    38→- `install.sh` dependency checks include relevant optional requirements.\n    39→\n    40→## Scenario Testing\n    41→\n    42→- `tests/<name>-agent/clean/scenario.env` exists and expects success.\n    43→- `tests/<name>-agent/issues/scenario.env` exists and expects failure.\n    44→- Fixtures are minimal but representative.\n    45→- `tests/run-scenarios.sh` can discover and run both scenarios.\n    46→\n    47→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01RpvTQ3WGywDJR35n94b4mq","session_id":"32a521e9-fb0e-42cc-9cbd-d9c4ff505402","uuid":"9ac2ddad-98d3-4013-b442-35b8e31e3691"}
