{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YF2D6KN3SShZ3xTt4rqSni","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# x-agent\n     2→\n     3→Every time your coding agent runs a lint or test cycle, it burns thousands of tokens on compilation progress and passing test names. x-agent cuts 90-97% of that noise — your agent gets structured pass/fail, you keep your context window for actual code.\n     4→\n     5→## Why?\n     6→\n     7→Standard build tools produce walls of text. Agents waste context window parsing noise. x-agent scripts give:\n     8→\n     9→- **Structured output** — `Step: lint`, `Result: PASS`, `Overall: FAIL`\n    10→- **Truncated diagnostics** — only the first N lines of errors/warnings (configurable)\n    11→- **Full logs on disk** — temp dir path printed so the agent can read more if needed\n    12→- **Consistent interface** — same env knobs and output format across all runners\n    13→\n    14→## Available Agents\n    15→\n    16→| Agent | Toolchain | Steps |\n    17→|-------|-----------|-------|\n    18→| `bash-agent` | Bash/Shell | syntax (bash -n), lint (shellcheck) |\n    19→| `cargo-agent` | Rust | fmt, check, clippy, test (nextest) |\n    20→| `docker-agent` | Docker | lint (hadolint), build-check (BuildKit) |\n    21→| `gha-agent` | GitHub Actions | lint (actionlint) |\n    22→| `go-agent` | Go | fmt (gofmt), vet, staticcheck, test |\n    23→| `helm-agent` | Helm | lint, template |\n    24→| `kube-agent` | Kubernetes | validate (kubeconform/kubeval) |\n    25→| `npm-agent` | Node.js | format, lint, typecheck, test, build |\n    26→| `py-agent` | Python | format (ruff/black), lint (ruff/flake8), typecheck (mypy/pyright), test (pytest) |\n    27→| `terra-agent` | Terraform | fmt (check/fix), safe init, plan-safe, validate, lint (tflint) |\n    28→\n    29→## Quick Start\n    30→\n    31→### Install via curl\n    32→\n    33→```sh\n    34→curl -sSf https://raw.githubusercontent.com/codesoda/x-agent/main/install.sh | sh\n    35→```\n    36→\n    37→### Install from local clone\n    38→\n    39→```sh\n    40→git clone git@github.com:codesoda/x-agent.git\n    41→cd x-agent\n    42→sh install.sh\n    43→```\n    44→\n    45→Local installs use symlinks so edits to the repo are immediately reflected.\n    46→The installer prompts for each x-agent skill so you can install only what you want.\n    47→It also prints a short AGENTS.md/CLAUDE.md policy snippet you can copy/paste.\n    48→\n    49→### Use directly (no install)\n    50→\n    51→```sh\n    52→# Rust project\n    53→path/to/x-agent/skills/cargo-agent/scripts/cargo-agent.sh\n    54→\n    55→# Node.js project\n    56→path/to/x-agent/skills/npm-agent/scripts/npm-agent.sh\n    57→\n    58→# Python project\n    59→path/to/x-agent/skills/py-agent/scripts/py-agent.sh\n    60→\n    61→# Docker project\n    62→path/to/x-agent/skills/docker-agent/scripts/docker-agent.sh\n    63→\n    64→# GitHub Actions project\n    65→path/to/x-agent/skills/gha-agent/scripts/gha-agent.sh\n    66→\n    67→# Go project\n    68→path/to/x-agent/skills/go-agent/scripts/go-agent.sh\n    69→\n    70→# Helm project\n    71→path/to/x-agent/skills/helm-agent/scripts/helm-agent.sh\n    72→\n    73→# Kubernetes project\n    74→path/to/x-agent/skills/kube-agent/scripts/kube-agent.sh\n    75→\n    76→# Terraform project\n    77→path/to/x-agent/skills/terra-agent/scripts/terra-agent.sh\n    78→```\n    79→\n    80→## Usage\n    81→\n    82→### bash-agent\n    83→\n    84→```sh\n    85→bash-agent.sh              # full suite: syntax + lint\n    86→bash-agent.sh syntax       # bash -n syntax check only\n    87→bash-agent.sh lint         # shellcheck lint only\n    88→SHELLCHECK_SEVERITY=error bash-agent.sh lint  # only errors, ignore warnings\n    89→```\n    90→\n    91→### cargo-agent\n    92→\n    93→```sh\n    94→cargo-agent.sh              # full suite: fmt + clippy + test\n    95→cargo-agent.sh fmt          # format only\n    96→cargo-agent.sh clippy       # clippy only\n    97→cargo-agent.sh test         # tests only\n    98→cargo-agent.sh test -p api  # tests in a specific crate\n    99→```\n   100→\n   101→### docker-agent\n   102→\n   103→```sh\n   104→docker-agent.sh                        # full suite: lint only (build-check off by default)\n   105→docker-agent.sh lint                   # hadolint check only\n   106→RUN_BUILD_CHECK=1 docker-agent.sh all  # lint + BuildKit check\n   107→```\n   108→\n   109→`docker-agent` discovers `Dockerfile`, `Dockerfile.*`, and `*.dockerfile` files recursively. `build-check` uses `docker build --check` (BuildKit lint mode) and defaults to OFF. Reports SKIP when no Dockerfiles are found.\n   110→\n   111→### gha-agent\n   112→\n   113→```sh\n   114→gha-agent.sh              # lint all workflow files\n   115→gha-agent.sh lint         # actionlint check only\n   116→```\n   117→\n   118→`gha-agent` runs `actionlint` on `.github/workflows/*.yml` and `*.yaml` files. Reports SKIP when no workflows directory exists.\n   119→\n   120→### go-agent\n   121→\n   122→```sh\n   123→go-agent.sh                 # full suite: fmt + vet + staticcheck + test\n   124→go-agent.sh fmt             # gofmt check/fix\n   125→go-agent.sh vet             # go vet analysis\n   126→go-agent.sh test            # tests only\n   127→FMT_MODE=fix go-agent.sh fmt  # auto-fix formatting\n   128→```\n   129→\n   130→`go-agent` uses `gofmt` for formatting (auto-fix locally, check-only in CI), `go vet` for analysis, optional `staticcheck` for linting, and `go test` for tests.\n   131→\n   132→### helm-agent\n   133→\n   134→```sh\n   135→helm-agent.sh              # full suite: lint + template\n   136→helm-agent.sh lint         # helm lint only\n   137→helm-agent.sh template     # helm template only\n   138→CHART_DIR=charts/myapp helm-agent.sh all  # explicit chart directory\n   139→```\n   140→\n   141→`helm-agent` auto-detects chart directories by searching for `Chart.yaml`. Use `CHART_DIR` to override. Reports SKIP when no charts are found.\n   142→\n   143→### kube-agent\n   144→\n   145→```sh\n   146→kube-agent.sh              # full suite: validate\n   147→kube-agent.sh validate     # validate manifests only\n   148→KUBE_SCHEMAS_DIR=path kube-agent.sh all  # custom schema location\n   149→```\n   150→\n   151→`kube-agent` auto-detects kubeconform or kubeval and validates all `.yaml`/`.yml` files containing Kubernetes resource definitions (`apiVersion:` + `kind:`). Use `KUBE_SCHEMAS_DIR` for custom schemas. Reports SKIP when no manifests are found.\n   152→\n   153→### npm-agent\n   154→\n   155→```sh\n   156→npm-agent.sh                # full suite: format + lint + typecheck + test + build\n   157→npm-agent.sh lint           # lint only\n   158→npm-agent.sh test           # tests only\n   159→npm-agent.sh typecheck      # type checking only\n   160→```\n   161→\n   162→npm-agent auto-detects your package manager (bun, pnpm, yarn, npm) and finds formatters/linters from package.json scripts or common tools (biome, eslint, prettier, tsc).\n   163→\n   164→### py-agent\n   165→\n   166→```sh\n   167→py-agent.sh                # full suite: format + lint + typecheck + test\n   168→py-agent.sh format         # format only (auto-fix locally, check in CI)\n   169→py-agent.sh lint           # lint only\n   170→py-agent.sh test           # tests only\n   171→py-agent.sh test -k login  # tests matching \"login\"\n   172→```\n   173→\n   174→py-agent auto-detects your runner (uv, poetry, or plain python) and finds tools (ruff, black, flake8, mypy, pyright, pytest).\n   175→\n   176→### terra-agent\n   177→\n   178→```sh\n   179→terra-agent.sh                              # full suite: fmt(check) + validate + lint\n   180→terra-agent.sh fmt-check                    # report formatting drift\n   181→terra-agent.sh fmt-fix                      # auto-fix formatting\n   182→terra-agent.sh init                         # safe non-mutating init\n   183→terra-agent.sh plan-safe                    # safe non-mutating plan\n   184→TERRAFORM_CHDIR=infra terra-agent.sh all    # run in infra/\n   185→FMT_MODE=fix terra-agent.sh fmt             # fmt using env-selected mode\n   186→```\n   187→\n   188→`terra-agent` init is safety-first by default: `-backend=false`, `-input=false`, `-get=false`, `-upgrade=false`, `-lockfile=readonly`, and temp `TF_DATA_DIR` so project files are not mutated.\n   189→`terra-agent` plan-safe uses `-refresh=false`, `-lock=false`, and passes on detailed exit code `2` (changes detected).\n   190→\n   191→## Environment Knobs\n   192→\n   193→All agents share the same pattern:\n   194→\n   195→| Variable | Default | Description |\n   196→|----------|---------|-------------|\n   197→| `RUN_<STEP>` | `1` | Set to `0` to skip a step |\n   198→| `MAX_LINES` | `40` | Max diagnostic lines printed per step |\n   199→| `KEEP_DIR` | `0` | Set to `1` to keep temp log dir on success |\n   200→\n   201→```sh\n   202→# Skip tests, keep logs\n   203→RUN_TESTS=0 KEEP_DIR=1 cargo-agent.sh\n   204→\n   205→# Only run lint and typecheck\n   206→RUN_FORMAT=0 RUN_TESTS=0 RUN_BUILD=0 npm-agent.sh\n   207→```\n   208→\n   209→## Output Format\n   210→\n   211→```\n   212→------------------------------------------------------------\n   213→Step: clippy\n   214→Errors: 0\n   215→Warnings: 3\n   216→\n   217→Diagnostics (first 40 lines):\n   218→warning: unused variable `x`\n   219→warning: unused import `std::io`\n   220→warning: function `old_handler` is never used\n   221→\n   222→Result: PASS\n   223→Full JSON: /tmp/cargo-agent.abc123/clippy.json\n   224→Lean diags: /tmp/cargo-agent.abc123/clippy.diags.txt\n   225→Time: 4s\n   226→------------------------------------------------------------\n   227→Overall: PASS\n   228→Logs: /tmp/cargo-agent.abc123\n   229→```\n   230→\n   231→On **PASS**, temp logs are cleaned up automatically. On **FAIL** (or `KEEP_DIR=1`), logs are preserved and the path is printed so the agent can inspect them.\n   232→\n   233→## Claude Code Skills\n   234→\n   235→The `skills/` directory contains Claude Code skill definitions. After installing, agents like Claude Code can invoke these as skills:\n   236→\n   237→- `/bash-agent` — run shell script checks\n   238→- `/cargo-agent` — run Rust checks\n   239→- `/docker-agent` — run Dockerfile linting\n   240→- `/gha-agent` — run GitHub Actions workflow linting\n   241→- `/go-agent` — run Go checks\n   242→- `/helm-agent` — run Helm chart checks\n   243→- `/kube-agent` — run Kubernetes manifest validation\n   244→- `/npm-agent` — run Node.js checks\n   245→- `/py-agent` — run Python checks\n   246→- `/terra-agent` — run Terraform checks/fixes\n   247→\n   248→## License\n   249→\n   250→MIT\n   251→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"32a521e9-fb0e-42cc-9cbd-d9c4ff505402","uuid":"b772b238-3c49-45bc-b60f-889cb729d443","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/README.md","content":"# x-agent\n\nEvery time your coding agent runs a lint or test cycle, it burns thousands of tokens on compilation progress and passing test names. x-agent cuts 90-97% of that noise — your agent gets structured pass/fail, you keep your context window for actual code.\n\n## Why?\n\nStandard build tools produce walls of text. Agents waste context window parsing noise. x-agent scripts give:\n\n- **Structured output** — `Step: lint`, `Result: PASS`, `Overall: FAIL`\n- **Truncated diagnostics** — only the first N lines of errors/warnings (configurable)\n- **Full logs on disk** — temp dir path printed so the agent can read more if needed\n- **Consistent interface** — same env knobs and output format across all runners\n\n## Available Agents\n\n| Agent | Toolchain | Steps |\n|-------|-----------|-------|\n| `bash-agent` | Bash/Shell | syntax (bash -n), lint (shellcheck) |\n| `cargo-agent` | Rust | fmt, check, clippy, test (nextest) |\n| `docker-agent` | Docker | lint (hadolint), build-check (BuildKit) |\n| `gha-agent` | GitHub Actions | lint (actionlint) |\n| `go-agent` | Go | fmt (gofmt), vet, staticcheck, test |\n| `helm-agent` | Helm | lint, template |\n| `kube-agent` | Kubernetes | validate (kubeconform/kubeval) |\n| `npm-agent` | Node.js | format, lint, typecheck, test, build |\n| `py-agent` | Python | format (ruff/black), lint (ruff/flake8), typecheck (mypy/pyright), test (pytest) |\n| `terra-agent` | Terraform | fmt (check/fix), safe init, plan-safe, validate, lint (tflint) |\n\n## Quick Start\n\n### Install via curl\n\n```sh\ncurl -sSf https://raw.githubusercontent.com/codesoda/x-agent/main/install.sh | sh\n```\n\n### Install from local clone\n\n```sh\ngit clone git@github.com:codesoda/x-agent.git\ncd x-agent\nsh install.sh\n```\n\nLocal installs use symlinks so edits to the repo are immediately reflected.\nThe installer prompts for each x-agent skill so you can install only what you want.\nIt also prints a short AGENTS.md/CLAUDE.md policy snippet you can copy/paste.\n\n### Use directly (no install)\n\n```sh\n# Rust project\npath/to/x-agent/skills/cargo-agent/scripts/cargo-agent.sh\n\n# Node.js project\npath/to/x-agent/skills/npm-agent/scripts/npm-agent.sh\n\n# Python project\npath/to/x-agent/skills/py-agent/scripts/py-agent.sh\n\n# Docker project\npath/to/x-agent/skills/docker-agent/scripts/docker-agent.sh\n\n# GitHub Actions project\npath/to/x-agent/skills/gha-agent/scripts/gha-agent.sh\n\n# Go project\npath/to/x-agent/skills/go-agent/scripts/go-agent.sh\n\n# Helm project\npath/to/x-agent/skills/helm-agent/scripts/helm-agent.sh\n\n# Kubernetes project\npath/to/x-agent/skills/kube-agent/scripts/kube-agent.sh\n\n# Terraform project\npath/to/x-agent/skills/terra-agent/scripts/terra-agent.sh\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n### bash-agent\n\n```sh\nbash-agent.sh              # full suite: syntax + lint\nbash-agent.sh syntax       # bash -n syntax check only\nbash-agent.sh lint         # shellcheck lint only\nSHELLCHECK_SEVERITY=error bash-agent.sh lint  # only errors, ignore warnings\n```\n\n### cargo-agent\n\n```sh\ncargo-agent.sh              # full suite: fmt + clippy + test\ncargo-agent.sh fmt          # format only\ncargo-agent.sh clippy       # clippy only\ncargo-agent.sh test         # tests only\ncargo-agent.sh test -p api  # tests in a specific crate\n```\n\n### docker-agent\n\n```sh\ndocker-agent.sh                        # full suite: lint only (build-check off by default)\ndocker-agent.sh lint                   # hadolint check only\nRUN_BUILD_CHECK=1 docker-agent.sh all  # lint + BuildKit check\n```\n\n`docker-agent` discovers `Dockerfile`, `Dockerfile.*`, and `*.dockerfile` files recursively. `build-check` uses `docker build --check` (BuildKit lint mode) and defaults to OFF. Reports SKIP when no Dockerfiles are found.\n\n### gha-agent\n\n```sh\ngha-agent.sh              # lint all workflow files\ngha-agent.sh lint         # actionlint check only\n```\n\n`gha-agent` runs `actionlint` on `.github/workflows/*.yml` and `*.yaml` files. Reports SKIP when no workflows directory exists.\n\n### go-agent\n\n```sh\ngo-agent.sh                 # full suite: fmt + vet + staticcheck + test\ngo-agent.sh fmt             # gofmt check/fix\ngo-agent.sh vet             # go vet analysis\ngo-agent.sh test            # tests only\nFMT_MODE=fix go-agent.sh fmt  # auto-fix formatting\n```\n\n`go-agent` uses `gofmt` for formatting (auto-fix locally, check-only in CI), `go vet` for analysis, optional `staticcheck` for linting, and `go test` for tests.\n\n### helm-agent\n\n```sh\nhelm-agent.sh              # full suite: lint + template\nhelm-agent.sh lint         # helm lint only\nhelm-agent.sh template     # helm template only\nCHART_DIR=charts/myapp helm-agent.sh all  # explicit chart directory\n```\n\n`helm-agent` auto-detects chart directories by searching for `Chart.yaml`. Use `CHART_DIR` to override. Reports SKIP when no charts are found.\n\n### kube-agent\n\n```sh\nkube-agent.sh              # full suite: validate\nkube-agent.sh validate     # validate manifests only\nKUBE_SCHEMAS_DIR=path kube-agent.sh all  # custom schema location\n```\n\n`kube-agent` auto-detects kubeconform or kubeval and validates all `.yaml`/`.yml` files containing Kubernetes resource definitions (`apiVersion:` + `kind:`). Use `KUBE_SCHEMAS_DIR` for custom schemas. Reports SKIP when no manifests are found.\n\n### npm-agent\n\n```sh\nnpm-agent.sh                # full suite: format + lint + typecheck + test + build\nnpm-agent.sh lint           # lint only\nnpm-agent.sh test           # tests only\nnpm-agent.sh typecheck      # type checking only\n```\n\nnpm-agent auto-detects your package manager (bun, pnpm, yarn, npm) and finds formatters/linters from package.json scripts or common tools (biome, eslint, prettier, tsc).\n\n### py-agent\n\n```sh\npy-agent.sh                # full suite: format + lint + typecheck + test\npy-agent.sh format         # format only (auto-fix locally, check in CI)\npy-agent.sh lint           # lint only\npy-agent.sh test           # tests only\npy-agent.sh test -k login  # tests matching \"login\"\n```\n\npy-agent auto-detects your runner (uv, poetry, or plain python) and finds tools (ruff, black, flake8, mypy, pyright, pytest).\n\n### terra-agent\n\n```sh\nterra-agent.sh                              # full suite: fmt(check) + validate + lint\nterra-agent.sh fmt-check                    # report formatting drift\nterra-agent.sh fmt-fix                      # auto-fix formatting\nterra-agent.sh init                         # safe non-mutating init\nterra-agent.sh plan-safe                    # safe non-mutating plan\nTERRAFORM_CHDIR=infra terra-agent.sh all    # run in infra/\nFMT_MODE=fix terra-agent.sh fmt             # fmt using env-selected mode\n```\n\n`terra-agent` init is safety-first by default: `-backend=false`, `-input=false`, `-get=false`, `-upgrade=false`, `-lockfile=readonly`, and temp `TF_DATA_DIR` so project files are not mutated.\n`terra-agent` plan-safe uses `-refresh=false`, `-lock=false`, and passes on detailed exit code `2` (changes detected).\n\n## Environment Knobs\n\nAll agents share the same pattern:\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `RUN_<STEP>` | `1` | Set to `0` to skip a step |\n| `MAX_LINES` | `40` | Max diagnostic lines printed per step |\n| `KEEP_DIR` | `0` | Set to `1` to keep temp log dir on success |\n\n```sh\n# Skip tests, keep logs\nRUN_TESTS=0 KEEP_DIR=1 cargo-agent.sh\n\n# Only run lint and typecheck\nRUN_FORMAT=0 RUN_TESTS=0 RUN_BUILD=0 npm-agent.sh\n```\n\n## Output Format\n\n```\n------------------------------------------------------------\nStep: clippy\nErrors: 0\nWarnings: 3\n\nDiagnostics (first 40 lines):\nwarning: unused variable `x`\nwarning: unused import `std::io`\nwarning: function `old_handler` is never used\n\nResult: PASS\nFull JSON: /tmp/cargo-agent.abc123/clippy.json\nLean diags: /tmp/cargo-agent.abc123/clippy.diags.txt\nTime: 4s\n------------------------------------------------------------\nOverall: PASS\nLogs: /tmp/cargo-agent.abc123\n```\n\nOn **PASS**, temp logs are cleaned up automatically. On **FAIL** (or `KEEP_DIR=1`), logs are preserved and the path is printed so the agent can inspect them.\n\n## Claude Code Skills\n\nThe `skills/` directory contains Claude Code skill definitions. After installing, agents like Claude Code can invoke these as skills:\n\n- `/bash-agent` — run shell script checks\n- `/cargo-agent` — run Rust checks\n- `/docker-agent` — run Dockerfile linting\n- `/gha-agent` — run GitHub Actions workflow linting\n- `/go-agent` — run Go checks\n- `/helm-agent` — run Helm chart checks\n- `/kube-agent` — run Kubernetes manifest validation\n- `/npm-agent` — run Node.js checks\n- `/py-agent` — run Python checks\n- `/terra-agent` — run Terraform checks/fixes\n\n## License\n\nMIT\n","numLines":251,"startLine":1,"totalLines":251}}}
