LES set but no YAML matches: emits `Result: SKIP (no YAML files in CHANGED_FILES)` and exits 0\n- No playbooks for syntax check: emits `Result: SKIP (no playbooks found for syntax check)` and exits 0\n- FMT_MODE=auto resolves to fix locally, check in CI\n- CI forces check mode even when FMT_MODE=fix\n- Invalid FMT_MODE exits with code 2\n- Unknown command prints usage and exits 2\n- help/--help/-h works without ansible-lint/ansible-playbook installed\n- Missing required tool exits with code 2\n- Per-playbook syntax checking with aggregate failure tracking\n- Recursive discovery excludes .git, node_modules, vendor, .venv, .cache, __pycache__\n\n## Tests written/run\n- 4 ansible-agent scenarios: all SKIP (ansible-lint not installed locally) — 0 failures\n- shellcheck --severity=warning passes on ansible-agent.sh\n- Manual verification: --help exits 0 without tools, missing tool exits 2\n\n## Known limitations\n- Scenarios require ansible-lint and ansible-playbook installed to run non-SKIP\n- Paths with spaces in CHANGED_FILES are not robustly handled (consistent with other agents)\n- ansible-lint version differences may produce different rule violations\n\n## Exploration notes\nUpdated `.ralph/exploration.md`:\n- Changed ansible-agent entry from \"planned (not yet implemented)\" to implemented with description of its actual patterns\n\n## Lessons Applied This Phase\n- Used docker-agent/gha-agent as primary pattern references for discovery-based agents\n- Exported CHANGED_FILES in scenario.env (learned from prior iterations — scenario harness runs agents as subprocess)\n- Kept clean fixtures minimal to avoid tool-version-dependent lint failures\n- Omitted setup_lock consistent with simple single-tool agents (gha-agent, docker-agent pattern)\n\n## Suggestions for the REVIEW agent\n- The scenarios are SKIP'd without ansible-lint/ansible-playbook installed — this is expected harness behavior\n- All shellcheck checks pass\n- The script follows the exact same patterns as docker-agent and gha-agent\n- FMT_MODE handling follows go-agent conventions\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":212,"cache_read_input_tokens":71801,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":212},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"32a521e9-fb0e-42cc-9cbd-d9c4ff505402","uuid":"a0f068e4-51b2-4df9-a651-ce5d0f72240a"}
